Fit Gear (Django E-commerce)
Description

GearHub is a basic e-commerce web application built using Django. The project focuses on core backend concepts such as authentication, authorization, CRUD operations, and user interactions. It allows users to browse sports equipment products (mainly gloves) and interact with them securely.

Features

User registration and login

Product listing with full CRUD operations

Comments and like/dislike functionality

Search products by keywords

Object-level permissions (users manage only their own content)

Customized Django admin panel

Tech Stack

Python

Django

Django ORM

SQLite (development)

HTML, CSS

Setup Instructions

Clone the repository

Create and activate a virtual environment

Install dependencies

Run migrations

Start the development server

python manage.py migrate
python manage.py runserver

Purpose

This project was built to strengthen understanding of Django fundamentals and real-world backend workflows, including authentication, permissions, relational models, and clean project structure.